div.div:
TMs were extracted from fresh spinach purchased at the local market. The spinach leaves were trimmed with removing stems and washed with deionized water. The leaves were ground and homogenized in a PBS 1 solution (pH 7.4, 10 mM PBS, 300 mM saccharide) using a blender (Cole-Parmer, 8011EG, Waring) at 22 000 rpm for 30 s. The homogenized solution was filtered with a nylon mesh. After centrifugation using a centrifuge (Avanti J-15R, Beckman Coulter, Inc.) at 4750 rpm for 15 min, the supernatant was removed, and the pellet was resuspended to the PBS 2 (pH 7.4, 10 mM PBS, 300 mM saccharide, 5 mM MgCl

 2

), followed by gently pipetting and rupturing the chloroplast membranes with the tip-sonicator (Q125, Qsonica LLC.). After centrifugation at 4750 rpm for 15 min, the supernatant was discarded, the pellet was resuspended to PBS 1 and ultracentrifuged at 20 000 rpm for 20 min followed by eliminating the supernatant. The pellet was resuspended and homogenized with PBS 3 (pH7.4, 10 mM PBS, 1.8 M saccharide), and PBS 4 (pH 7.4, 10 mM PBS, 1.3 M saccharide) was added to upper part followed by conducting the ultracentrifugation (XPN-100, Beckman Coulter, Inc.) at 38 000 rpm for 60 min. Then, TM pellets, was separated by density difference, was once again resuspended and centrifuged for washing of TMs at 20 000 rpm for 20 min. After leaving the pellet, the extracted TMs stored in a refrigerator at 4 °C before use. All centrifugation processes were conducted at 4 °C.

